section.text:

Symptoms associated with discontinuation of paroxetine tablets have been reported (see 
                           PRECAUTIONS:   Discontinuation of Treatment With Paroxetine Tablets
                        ). Patients should be monitored for these symptoms when discontinuing treatment, regardless of the indication for which paroxetine tablets is being prescribed. A gradual reduction in the dose rather than abrupt cessation is recommended whenever possible. If intolerable symptoms occur following a decrease in the dose or upon discontinuation of treatment, then resuming the previously prescribed dose may be considered. Subsequently, the physician may continue decreasing the dose but at a more gradual rate.
